comments: I strongly believe the Natives have too much control on the Fisheries, the Fisheries are afraid to prosecute them and therefore anything goes. I see the Natives selling fish on the side of the road, when this fish is meant to be consumed by them. They take more than they can use and it often ends up wasted, they also take the spawning salmon right out of the rivers just before they are about to spawn. The ruling that allows the Natives to take fish for ceremony is arbitrary, there is no clear definition of how much, how often so the Natives abuse this right and the Fisheries are powerless to stop them. Secondly stop the Atlantic fish farming, how can you have a detailed survey and leave out one of the most important aspects of our Pacific coastal waters. Finally the other important item that you left out of your survey is oil tankers, all this talk of carbon and clean water won't mean a thing should we have a oil tanker spill.
